Implement EXTENSION-015: GitHub Actions CI/CD

Context: We need automated builds for 6 platforms (darwin-x64/arm64, win32-x64/arm64, linux-x64/arm64) with testing and VSIX packaging.

Your task: Create GitHub Actions workflow for multi-platform builds, testing, and releases.

What to Build:

1. Workflow File (.github/workflows/extension-ci.yml):
- Trigger: push to main, PRs, tags (v*)
- Matrix build: 6 platforms
- Steps: checkout, setup Node, install deps, build, test, package, upload

2. Build Matrix:
platforms:
  - os: macos-latest, target: darwin-x64
  - os: macos-latest, target: darwin-arm64
  - os: windows-latest, target: win32-x64
  - os: windows-latest, target: win32-arm64
  - os: ubuntu-latest, target: linux-x64
  - os: ubuntu-latest, target: linux-arm64

3. VSIX Packaging:
- Use @vscode/vsce
- Package per platform: arela-{version}-{platform}.vsix
- Include platform-specific server binaries

4. Testing:
- Run TypeScript compilation
- Run linting
- Run unit tests (if any)
- Verify VSIX structure

5. Release:
- On tag push (v*), create GitHub release
- Upload all 6 VSIX files
- Generate release notes from commits

6. Scripts (packages/extension/package.json):
- "package": "vsce package"
- "package:all": script to package all platforms

Acceptance Criteria:
- CI runs on every push/PR
- Builds succeed for all 6 platforms
- VSIX files generated per platform
- Tests pass before packaging
- Releases auto-created on version tags
- Artifacts uploaded to GitHub releases

Build this now!


