Implement EXTENSION-019: Advanced Context Features

Context: Basic context (selection, workspace) works. Now add deep IDE context: diagnostics, symbols, type info, references.

Your task: Add advanced context features that leverage VS Code's language services.

What to Build:

1. Diagnostics Context (packages/extension/src/context/diagnostics.ts):
- Get diagnostics for active file
- Filter by severity (errors, warnings)
- Format for AI: file, line, message, severity
- Command: "Arela: Add Diagnostics Context"

2. Symbol Search (packages/extension/src/context/symbols.ts):
- Search workspace symbols
- Find definitions, references
- Format: name, kind, location, signature
- Command: "Arela: Find Symbol"

3. Type Information (packages/extension/src/context/types.ts):
- Get type at cursor position
- Show type definition
- Include JSDoc comments
- Command: "Arela: Show Type Info"

4. Go to Definition (packages/extension/src/context/definition.ts):
- Find definition of symbol at cursor
- Include definition code
- Show file path and line
- Auto-add to context

5. Find References (packages/extension/src/context/references.ts):
- Find all references to symbol
- Group by file
- Show usage count
- Command: "Arela: Find References"

6. Context Pills UI:
- Diagnostics pill (show error/warning count)
- Symbol pill (show symbol name)
- Type pill (show type signature)
- References pill (show reference count)

7. System Prompt Integration:
- Add diagnostics before code
- Add type info with code
- Add references after code
- Format clearly for AI

Acceptance Criteria:
- Can add diagnostics to context
- Can search and add symbols
- Can show type information
- Can find and add references
- All context types show as pills
- AI receives formatted context
- Works with TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, Go

Build this now!



Implement EXTENSION-020: Performance Optimization

Context: Extension works but needs optimization for speed, memory, and bundle size.

Your task: Optimize performance across the board: lazy loading, caching, virtual scrolling, memory management.

What to Build:

1. Lazy Loading (packages/extension/webview/):
- Lazy load heavy components (Settings, ConversationList)
- Code split by route
- Defer non-critical imports
- Target: <100ms initial load

2. Message Virtualization (packages/extension/webview/components/MessageList.svelte):
- Use virtual scrolling for long conversations
- Render only visible messages
- Recycle DOM nodes
- Target: 60fps with 1000+ messages

3. Caching (packages/extension/src/chat-provider.ts):
- Cache workspace context (invalidate on file changes)
- Cache model lists (TTL: 1 hour)
- Cache file contents (invalidate on edit)
- Use LRU cache (max 100 items)

4. Debouncing:
- Debounce selection updates (300ms)
- Debounce workspace scans (500ms)
- Debounce search queries (200ms)

5. Bundle Optimization (packages/extension/webview/vite.config.ts):
- Tree shaking
- Minification
- Code splitting
- Remove unused dependencies
- Target: <50KB gzipped per bundle

6. Memory Management:
- Dispose webview listeners on close
- Clear message history after 100 messages
- Limit conversation storage (max 50)
- Cleanup old conversations (>30 days)

7. Monitoring:
- Add performance marks
- Log slow operations (>1s)
- Track memory usage
- Report to console in dev mode

Acceptance Criteria:
- Initial load <100ms
- Message list renders 1000+ messages at 60fps
- Workspace scan <500ms
- Bundle size <50KB gzipped
- Memory usage <100MB
- No memory leaks
- Smooth scrolling and interactions

Build this now!